NASSAU, Bahamas (AP) -- Hurricane Floyd strengthened to a very  dangerous Category 4 storm today with 155 mph wind, surprising forecasters and charging toward the Bahamas on a path that also threatened the Florida coast.
MIAMI _ A hurricane that meteorologists said was four times thesize of the infamous Andrew and potentially even more destructivepounded toward Florida Monday, forcing hundreds of thousands fromtheir homes and leaving countless residents to hope that themassive storm would somehow miss their cities.
``This hurricane,'' said Jerry Jarrell, director of the NationalHurricane Center, ``could be catastrophic.''
